  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq">
    <h3>How should a restaurant respond to a bad review?</h3>
    <p>Thank the reviewer, acknowledge the specific issue, apologise without being defensive, and invite them to contact you offline to resolve it. Never argue publicly.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>How long should a restaurant review response be?</h3>
    <p>Between 50 and 150 words. Concise and genuine beats long and corporate every time.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq" style="border:none">
    <h3>Do restaurant review responses help Google ranking?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Google rewards businesses that respond to all reviews with higher local ranking. Restaurants with high response rates consistently appear higher in Google Maps searches.</p>
